news.title: NCLT approves Macrotech Developers' resolution plan for V Hotels
news.para: Under the resolution plan, Macrotech Developers will pay Rs 900 crore in tranches over a period of 270 days. The first tranche of Rs 90 crore has already been remitted.

news.title: Check FEMA regulations before buying property in Dubai
news.para: Deals offering easy payment plans with instalments over years may violate FEMA. Regulations permit remittance of $250,000 per individual annually for property purchases abroad.

news.title: Brookfield plans $10 billion investment in Indian real estate in 3-5 years
news.para: Brookfield--one of the largest office owners and operators in India—currently has a portfolio spanning more than 51 million sq ft across seven key Indian cities.

news.title: Ludhiana improvement trust ordered to pay Rs 1 lakh for delaying flat possession for 14 years
news.para: ​The commission has ordered the LIT to pay the compensation within 30 days from the date of receipt of copy of order to Hem Raj Kapila of Gill road, failing which they shall be further held liable to pay interest on the said amount at the rate 8% per annum from the date of order till actual payment.

news.title: Bengaluru: C&D processing plants in Chikkajala & Kannur not getting enough waste
news.para: The final notice was issued on March 27, stating, “Upon several intimations through notices, no serious compliance was observed. Hence, it is being recommended to KSPCB for further necessary action in accordance with the provision of the Environment (Prote­ction) Act 1986…”

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation seeks AAI's NOC for residential complex
news.para: As the two-acre plot falls within the airport's ‘red zone’, where there are limitations on construction activities due to its close proximity to aircraft landing, the civic body had to approach the AAI for a No Objection Certificate (NOC).

news.title: Will ask experts, use tech for in-situ rehabilitation of slums: Piyush Goyal
news.para: Under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY), we provided houses to four crore people, and three crore more will receive houses. Similarly, we will provide in-situ housing for slums.”

news.title: MahaRERA mandates strict parking regulations to prevent disputes
news.para: Following the registration of apartments, realty developers are mandated to incorporate these specifics into the allotment letter and agreement for sale, ensuring transparency and adherence to regulations.

news.title: Telangana HC asks officials to submit lake records over realty project in buffer zone
news.para: Telangana high court criticizes state for lax response to PIL accusing Vasavi Infra of building towers in Komatikunta lake buffer zone. Officials directed to submit lake records by April 30. Akula Satish accuses HMDA of allowing towers in FTL.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate loss widens to Rs 1,038 crore in FY24
news.para: Indiabulls Real Estate's total income also fell to Rs 468.75 crore during 2023-24 from Rs 648.47 crore in the preceding year, according to a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Sweden's Oscar Properties loss widens to $127.95 million in Q4 2023
news.para: Oscar Properties' losses after tax widened to 1.4 billion Swedish crowns ($127.95 million) in the final three months of 2023 as the company grappled with a nationwide real estate market crisis, from a year earlier loss of 400.9 million crowns.

news.title: Berkshire Hathaway's realty firm to pay $250 million to settle real estate commission lawsuits
news.para: HomeServices of America said Friday that the proposed settlement would shield its 51 brands, nearly 70,000 real estate agents and over 300 franchisees from similar litigation.

news.title: Bengaluru: Sub-registrar in soup for registering sale deeds without OCs
news.para: The builder must submit the occupancy certificate and khata certificate to the sub-registrar while registering the sale deed.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces posts net profit of Rs 71.48 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 54.60 crore, a dip of 79.80 per cent from Rs 270.26 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Court summons Ansal Properties' managing director in criminal intimidation case
news.para: ​Pranav Ansal is the vice chairman and managing director at Ansal Properties and Infrastructure Ltd. He is the son of real estate tycoon Sushil Ansal.

news.title: Oscar Properties chair departs as bondholders demand repayment
news.para: The statement followed news that holders of its senior unsecured bonds were seeking immediate repayment of some 884 million Swedish crowns ($81 million).

news.title: Austria's Signa sells Venice's Hotel Bauer to German group
news.para: Signa, the property group founded by Rene Benko, has become the biggest casualty so far in Europe's real estate crisis, with creditors filing claims totalling billions of euros.

news.title: Property registrations in Kolkata up 17% in March 2024: Report
news.para: In March 2024, the Kolkata Metropolitan Region witnessed a significant increase in apartment registrations, with 3,936 units registered, marking a 17% year-on-year growth, as reported by Knight Frank.

news.title: Lohia Global enters into real estate sector with Rs 1,000 crore investment
news.para: Lohia Global plans to invest Rs 1,000 crore in five residential projects spread across 30 lakh sq ft area in Moradabad, Lucknow, and Delhi-NCR. These projects will be developer in the next five years.

news.title: No building registration without sanctioned plan: Calcutta HC
news.para: A division bench of Chief Justice T S Sivagnanam and Hiranmay Bhattacharyya passed the order while taking note of the fact that the under-construction building that collapsed in the Garden Reach area had no sanction plan.
